Find the greatest common divisor of $10293$ and $29384$.

We can use the Euclidean algorithm to find the greatest common divisor of $10293$ and $29384$.

$$\begin{align*}
29384 &= 2 \cdot 10293 + 8998\\
10293 &= 1 \cdot 8998 + 1295\\
8998 &= 6 \cdot 1295 + 988\\
1295 &= 1 \cdot 988 + 307\\
988 &= 3 \cdot 307 + 101\\
307 &= 3 \cdot 101 + 6\\
101 &= 16 \cdot 6 + 5\\
6 &= 1 \cdot 5 + 1\\
5 &= 5 \cdot 1 + 0.
\end{align*}$$ Therefore, the greatest common divisor of $10293$ and $29384$ is $\boxed{1}$.

&=\text{gcd}\,(1323,172)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(1323-172 \cdot 7 ,172)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(119,172)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(119,172-119)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(119,53)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(119-53 \cdot 2,53)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(13,53).\\
